# Git Standards

## Commit Messages
- **Concise**: Keep commit messages short and focused. One line is preferred unless the change is highly complex.
- **No Self-Tagging**: Do not include "Co-authored-by" or any other mentions of the AI in the commit message.
- **Style**: Use the imperative mood (e.g., "Add contact page" instead of "Added contact page").

## Workflow
- Only commit when explicitly asked by the user.
- Group related changes into a single commit.
- Do not use verbose bullet points in commit messages unless requested.
